 \mathrm{\beta}(x,y) = \int_0^1t^{x-1}(1-t)^{y-1}\,dt \quad \textrm{Re}(x), \textrm{Re}(y) > 0. 
I= \int_{0}^{n}x^{s-1}\left(1-\frac{x}{n}\right)^n dx=n^s \int_{0}^{1}x^{s-1}\left(1-y\right)^n dy=n^s\beta(s,n+1)
=\Gamma(s)\,n^s\frac{\Gamma(n+1)}{\Gamma(n+1+s)}\sim \Gamma(s)\,n^s n^{-s}=\Gamma(s) 
 \implies \lim_{n\to \infty}I=\Gamma(s). 
 n! =\Gamma(n+1) \sim \left(\frac{n}{e}\right)^n\sqrt{2 \pi n}.  
